sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K390001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: 5'UTR and native RBS from psbA2 in Synechocystis sp. PCC 6803
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This is the 5'UTR and RBS region from gene psbA2 in Synechocystis sp. PCC 6803. It covers the entire region from the end of the promoter (as reported in Imamura S and Asayama M. 2009. Sigma Factors for Cyanobacterial Transcription. Gene Regulation and Systems Biology 3: 65-87) to immediately before the start codon of the psbA2 gene.
This part can serve as a general RBS for Synechocystis sp. PCC 6803, until a library of RBS strengths in PCC 6803 is assembled. The psbA2 gene codes for the photosystem II D1 protein in this species, and therefore we assume (and plan to verify) that the RBS strength is moderate to strong, due to the high requirement for this protein in photosynthesis.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Cody Tramp
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Genomic sequences from Synechocystis sp. PCC 6803
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We decided to go with the full region from the promoter to the start codon. This means that, with the addition of the biobrick scar, the RBS may be located farther from the start codon then is optimal. We plan to determine optimum spacing of the RBS in Synechocystis sp. PCC 6803 in future work.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I712019
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Firefly luciferase - luciferase from Photinus pyralis
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Firefly luciferase is luciferase from Photinus pyralis. By oxidation of substrate luciferin light is produced. Luciferase thus acts as a reporter protein when connected to other proteins or promoters.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Anja Korenčič
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This firefly luciferase comes from Promega PGL3 vector.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Part is cloned into pSBAK3 vector with terminator.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
